               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331017-138-person1327">
                  HENRY 
                  SANDERS
               <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1327" type="surname" value="SANDERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1327" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1327" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Samuel Adams, he is a <rs id="t18331017-138-viclabel754" type="occupation">hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331017-138-victim1326 t18331017-138-viclabel754"></join>. On the evening of the 4th of October, about nine o'clock, the prisoner came to buy a hat; I showed him several; I asked him 6s. 6d. for this one, he offered me 6s., which I agreed to take; he then said he wanted it made more fashionable - more narrow in front; I went to the end of the shop to get the iron to do it, when I missed the prisoner and the hat - I went out and turned up a court by the side of our house, where I saw him with the hat - I pursued him, and called, "Stop thief;" I did not lose sight of him till he was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331017-138-person1328">
                  GEORGE 
                  HARTLEY
               <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1328" type="surname" value="HARTLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1328" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1328" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was going up Elder-street, and heard the cry of "Stop thief;" I saw the prisoner running, with this hat in his hand; I stopped him, and this witness came and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331017-138-person1329">
                  GEORGE 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18331017-138-person1329" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
